Please find enclosed UPBGE 0.3 Pinball V3.2000 Game Upgrade (Recommended Graphic Card Nvidia Gforce 2070 & an intel i7).

1 - 4 Player selection,1 -3 Ball selection, High score Board, Targets & loop rankers, Loop circuit, Ball saver, Auto plunger, Bonus scores,
Dmd animations, Table Animations, Ball color change, MultiBall, Ball Trailer, Plunger Lane & Spinner hinge actuators.

- 3.2000 Upgrade -
1. Bug fixes.
2. Finalized the ball color code. (ball image trailer color now will match the ball color)
3. Game physic tweaks.

- 3.1994 Upgrade -
1. Reconfigured the BallTrailer Image Nodes.
2. Upgraded the BallTrailer Images.
3. Introduced a MouseMoveP1ball1.py for table hit object testing. F9 activates the code.
4. Some bug fixes.
5. Game physic tweaks.
6. Plunger, Flipper left & Right will deactivate the mouse move ball & mouse move camera code.
7. Updated the User key guide to reflect changes.

- 3.195 Upgrade -
1. Changed the 'Rotate To "Rot Axis" to X' which corrected the ball image trailer bug'

– 3.194 Upgrade –
1. Bug fixes.
2. Added ‘Align Axis to Vector & Rotate To’ to the ball image trailer Nodes

– 3.16 upgrade –
1. Bug fixes.
2. New ball trailers with image runner & alpha nodes introduced.
3. Animation ball color change replaces nodes.
4. Improved the frames per second performance.

Notes
1. In ‘Render Properties’ do not check the ‘Use Viewport Render box’ : else the replacemesh() api code fails to run.
2. In ‘Game Play Camera Mode’ under ‘Viewport Shading’ check that the ‘Scene Lights’ check box has been checked : else the lights will not function.
3. In Edit / Preferences / Addons check Game Engine Logic Nodes. Else ball trailer nodes will not run.

Please enjoy & rob what you can from it if you wish.

Upgrades with bug fixes to Pinball V3.2000 can be downloaded from:

https://www.dropbox.com/s/3w0agtlakvne1ag/UPGBE%20Pinball%20V3.2000.blend?dl=0
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d5zqF_syv0Y&feature=youtu.be

Load the game using UPBGE(0.3). The Game mode will show first (Out off Edit Mode Press 'P' or standalone start to get it up & running) 

Keyboard instruction will appear & the rest is all down to the user.

VP forum holds four more tables that I have worked on: PacMan, TexasPoker, Invader & Skittles which may appeal to you. 
It is a visual basic coded-driven pinball game. It's all freeware for non-profit use only. 
You may also find them with AtGames if they are still using them. 

